result.execSummary:
The defendant Zachary Edwin Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Zachary Edwin Williams is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Zachary Edwin Williams was found guilty of Disorderly conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury]. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
